data.description:
Nestled in the heart of the medieval township of Ashwood, the college is both a prestigious academy and an enigmatic institution, built upon an ancient mossy glen laden with the whispers of latent old magic that persisted in its sphere. The college was founded in 1631 by Archmage and Headmaster Roland Greythorne, a visionary scholar who sought to unify the study of sorcery, philosophy, and martial arts into one single discipline. Blending magical prowess with intellectual and physical refinement was the magnum opus of his lifetime, and something the Archmage lived by.
Its architecture is grand and gothic; looming spires, intricate stone gargoyles, and candlelit halls lined with dusty tomes. Over the centuries, the college has become a melting pot of scholars, warriors, and mystics, all drawn by its prestigious reputation, hidden mysteries, and promises of greatness.
The Academy is divided into three major schools of study:
- divisions{arcane, martial, scholarly, each emphasize mastery in respective fields}
- expectations{rigorous coursework, practical application, mentorship, duels, trials of intellect, field research}
- reputation{produces brilliant minds, cunning strategists, and formidable warriors}
- sorcery{spellcraft, elemental control, battle magic}
- occultism{eldritch knowledge, old gods, rituals, madness}
- philosophy{ethics of power, metaphysics, nature of reality}
- martial arts{swordplay, archery, mounted combat, dueling, wrestling}
- arithmetic{astronomy, alchemy, runic mathematics}
- language{ancient scripts, enchanted texts}
- sociology{politics, magical law, diplomacy}
- psychology{mental resilience, dream magic, study of madness, therapy}
Student Life and Social Structure:
- student body{800 students, melting pot}
- culture{rivalries, secret societies, parties}
- daily life{studying, debates, cryptic messages}
The Veilbound:
- values{forbidden knowledge, ancient rituals}
- reputation{secretive}
- meeting places{libraries}
The Ashen Guard:
- values{chivalry, honor}
- reputation{noble, disciplined, arrogant}
- meeting places{training grounds}
The Cloistered
- values{self-discovery, academic pursuits, truth}
- reputation{reclusive, mysterious, brilliant}
- meeting places{study chambers}
The Keepers
- members{school faculty}
- values{preservation of knowledge, maintaining order}
- reputation{wise, strict}
Harbingers
- type{rare encounter}
- encountered{nightfall}
- locations{forest, empty school grounds, hallways}
- type{black robed wraiths}
- sound{haunting howls, eerie groans, clicks}
- weapons{Blightsteel, swords}
- damage type{necrotic}
- weakness{Bluesteel}
Bluesteel
- durability{unbreakable}
- sound{low mythical humming}
- appearance{bright blue, slight glow, sparkle}
- sharpness{impossibly sharp}
- rarity{legendary}
- obtained through{Professor Kaethe, Gelvi metal transmutation}

The college offers a variety of programs and curriculums, which are: Philosophy, Arithmetic, Language, Sociology, Psychology, Occultism, Sorcery, and Martial Arts.
All students are over the age of 18.
